A client/server software package allowing remote network access to graphical desktops.

== Installation ==

=== USE flags ===

{{USEflag|package=net-misc/tigervnc}}

=== Emerge ===

Those using the package for the VNC server need to install the package with the <code>server</code> USE flag enabled. This can be added to the {{Path|[[:/etc/portage/package.use|package.use]]}} file (or directory), or specified one-shot-like on the command-line:

{{RootCmd|USE{{=}}"server" emerge --ask --update --newuse net-misc/tigervnc}}

{{Note|Setting <code>USE{{=}}"server"</code> as displayed in the example above will install the package with the specified USE flags, however they will not be preserved upon package upgrades. Be sure to set them in {{Path|package.use}} in order to make flags persist.}}

Those installing just the client can simply emerge the package:

{{Emerge|net-misc/tigervnc}}

== Configuration ==

Login with normal user:

{{Cmd|vncpasswd}}

{{Cmd|vncserver}}

Kill the running vncserver:

{{Cmd|pkill Xvnc}}

Setup the displays:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/conf.d/vnc|1=
DISPLAYS="user:1 user2:2"
}}

=== Special configuration for KDE (and some others) installed on server ===

Edit the vnc startup script:

{{FileBox|filename=~/.vnc/xstartup|lang=bash|1=
#!/bin/sh
startkde &
#startxfce4 &
#startfluxbox &
#fvwm2 &
#icewm-session &
#startlxde &
#xfce4-panel &
}}

=== Special configuration for lxterminal installed on server ===

Edit the vnc startup script:

{{FileBox|filename=~/.vnc/xstartup|lang=bash|1=
#!/bin/sh
xrdb $HOME/.Xresources
xsetroot -solid black
lxterminal &
/usr/bin/lxsession -s LXDE &
}}

=== Special configuration for twm installed on server ===

Edit the vnc startup script:

{{FileBox|filename=~/.vnc/xstartup|lang=bash|1=
#!/bin/sh
xrdb $HOME/.Xresources
xsetroot -solid grey
xterm -geometry 80x24+10+10 -ls -title "$VNCDESKTOP Desktop" &
twm &
}}

Make sure you set the xstartup file to be executable (chmod +x):

{{Cmd|chmod +x ~/.vnc/xstartup}}

